Full text: https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc/4.0/legalcode
Human-readable summary: https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc/4.0/

You are free to:

- **Share** — copy and redistribute these designs in any medium or format.
- **Adapt** — remix, transform, and build upon them.

Under the following terms:

- **Attribution** — You must give appropriate credit ("PindouVerse",
  https://github.com/cangelzz/pindouverse), provide a link to this license,
  and indicate if changes were made.
- **NonCommercial** — You may not use these designs for commercial purposes.
  This includes (but is not limited to):
  - Selling, sublicensing, or otherwise distributing the sample design
    files or images derived from them.
  - Producing physical bead artwork from these specific sample designs
    for sale, advertising, or any commercial promotion.
  - Including these designs in any paid product, service, course, or
    subscription.

This non-commercial restriction is intentional. These samples are provided
so users can verify the software, learn the file format, and try features
— not as commercial assets.

Note that this license applies to the **sample designs only**. The
PindouVerse software itself is licensed separately under the PolyForm
Noncommercial License 1.0.0; see `../LICENSE` and `../LICENSE-CODE` at the
repository root.

Carve-out clarification (software, not these samples)
-----------------------------------------------------

A separate clarification in the root `LICENSE` notes that individuals
who use the PindouVerse software to design and physically produce their
own bead artwork may sell that physical artwork without it being treated
as Commercial Use of the software. That clarification applies to designs
**you create yourself** with the software. It does NOT extend to the
sample designs in this directory — these specific designs remain
governed by the CC BY-NC 4.0 NonCommercial restriction above.

Commercial Licensing
--------------------

For commercial licensing of any sample design, open a GitHub issue at
https://github.com/cangelzz/pindouverse/issues with the label
`commercial-license` describing your intended use.
